No few than 500 households in Osun State have been assisted with foodstuffs to assist them in the Ramadan fast. The beneficiaries drawn from different communities in the state received the food stuff at designated locations in Osogbo, Ido-Osun, Inisha, Ejigbo and Ifon under strict compliance with social distancing. Some of the beneficiaries include the Persons with Disabilities, (PWD), pregnant women, aged, widows and indigent families. Tagged “Ramadan 1441 A.H/2020 CE Iftar,” the programme was funded by Kuwait Awqaf Public Foundation and Kuwait Embassy in Nigeria. Dear valued readers, subscribe to the Daily Trust e-paper to continue enjoying our diet of authoritative news. Kindly subscribe here It was facilitated by SIBGHATUL-LAAHI Center for Islamic Education and Arabic Studies located at Makkah-Madinah area, Ajegunle, Ido-Osun. The chairman of the center, Sheikh Zakariyah Akanji Sanusi, said the gesture was aimed at assisting the beneficiaries during the holy month of Ramadan.  Beneficiaries of Osun free train ride hail Aregbesola Pious Muslim Women to feed 2,000 faithful during Ramadan Sokoto Ramadan feeding raises dust